{
  "doc_id": "8831",
  "text": "Flow-cytometric applications using different dyes have been compared to standard methods to assess yeast cultures in baking, wine making, cider making, and brewing [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] . The technique has also been used to study the membrane integrity of ethanol-stressed Oenococcus oeni cells [CITATION_9] . Most studies of FC applications have focused mainly on microorganims as pure cultures, and only a small number have analyzed mixed populations over time [CITATION_10] .",
